SIMPLE: harshness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harshness
<hw>Harsh"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
harsh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, she is⟦br⟧
Ten times more gentle than her father's crabbed,⟦br⟧
And he's composed of <qex>harshness</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'Tis not enough no <qex>harshness</qex> gives offense,⟦br⟧
The sound must seem an echo to the sense.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Acrimony; roughness; sternness; asperity;
tartness. See <er>Acrimony</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harslet</ent>⟦br⟧
